ENTITY_CREATE - Developer

ENTITY_CREATE
event type
Â¶
ENTITY_CREATE
events are emitted whenever an
asset
is created in Atlan.
One
ENTITY_CREATE
event is emitted for each asset that is created
So, for example, if the Snowflake crawler runs and creates:
1 connection
3 databases
10 schemas
500 tables
15,000 columns
Atlan will emit 15,514
ENTITY_CREATE
events â€” one for each of these assets.
The details of the created asset will be in the
message.entity
portion of the event payload.
